I decided to move to a new city to romanticise my life & it kinda got too stressful to romanticise (fatt k chauhatar ho gaya)🤣

I landed on 15th Jan with full delulu & god’s favourite child, “new girl in the city” vibrations to bunk at my friend’s place @rishi_dokania.
I had watched reels about Bangalore house hunt situation but a girl with NYC dreams thought how tough would it be? NYC ka toh ni pata Bangalore ka rent market is traumatising.

I keep wondering, if renting is so tough how do people even buy a house in this economy.

It got kinda sappy story, especially atter the spooky flatmate story & I almost packed my stuff to go back to Delhi but now it became a challenge, the Aquarius in me couldn’t deter & I got friends who always hype me to get to anything I want, grateful to have @rishi_kedia @eftesaam @siddhi_sanguri @mayuriichaurasiia 
@aishi_saun @tushar_kedia @_akanshasethi & cuto @ishanyaya <3

Cut to today, writing this caption from the balcony of my cute lil 1BHK. Loving the Bangalore’s weather & planning to train for my first 5k marathon with @abhilashasuman, go to startup community meet-ups because it’s the city of startups, fix my sleep hygiene, work on my ebook, take 1:1 consultantion calls, be better at my full time job & so much more 💪☁️🫧

Thora late hi sahi! The new journey begins here 🚀

hi i’m dr kajal.
i don’t work in clinics anymore but i still call myself “Dr” cuz i earned that degree 💅

saying it out loud still gives me shivers.
i switched my career in jan. it’s been 4 months.
i still feel shy calling myself a creative director & marketing specialist, i learnt most of it from making silly reels on instagram 🥲

I am hired at my current workplace for being a doctor who has creative social media skills. 

like how does this combo even make sense?

i’m still figuring it out.
meri abhi bhi fati padi hai.
but i LOVE LOVE LOVBEBBEBEBEVEVEVEVEE my life.🫶🏻☁️
i love waking up to my to-do list.
i love working from home, from cafes, from balconies, from anywhere. I LOVE HOW I HAVE TIME FOR THINGS THAT FILLS MY CUP. 

from college fees debt, borrowing money from my friends, to building an emergency fund and moving into a fully furnished 1BHK.⛅️
from shrinking in conversations
to becoming the one who initiates them.

Sabse Upar: I’m proud of myself.
For taking a stand for what I needed.
For going against my mom’s fears, my relatives’ opinions, my friends’ advice… and even the expectations of some of you here.

Their demons ain’t mine 😮‍💨

This is my life now.
And I’m so glad I didn’t wait for permission🕊️

I quit the job I spent years working for 👩🏻‍⚕️

Working as a doctor didn’t feel like the version of medicine I once dreamed about. Especially after the RGKAR Kolkata case, I couldn’t glamourise the toxicity 🙇🏻‍♀️

I left working at Safdarjung, moved into my bsf place in Noida @siddhi_sanguri, borrowed a bed for 6 months, & quietly started rebranding my life ✨

These 5 shifts helped me rebuild, from scratch:

1. I faced my money story 💰 & built work that gave me freedom: I realised I had scarcity money mindset.  Instead of managing money better, I kept trying to make more & getting into the loop of debt. I found the balance
I started freelancing: content writing, social media gigs, whatever I could do from my iPad
Eventually that led me to a full time role as Creative Director at a US based brand (they even gave me a mac, workstation upgrade!)
Now I work remotely, earn on the go, & still get to do things I love : like cooking Thai curry for friends or testing five versions of guacamole just because I can 🥘 

2. I didn’t try to fix everything at once. I started by fixing my morning routine. 
D iagnosed the burnout.
O wned the new me, disowned the halo effect that comes w medicine for the society.
C reated boundaries.
T uned into my body: running, swimming, Pilates 🛼
O rganised my meal plan (protein)
R ewired my mind to believe in God’s plan. I was an atheist for most of my life & now I pray sometimes. 

3. I moved to a new city
I wanted a fresh start. Mumbai or Bangalore. Everyone said Mumbai was too expensive so I came to Bangalore (but Blore is expensive bruh)
The video above is from one of those temporary BnBs. Still house hunting, should update soon ☁️

4. I found my people & a soft space
@medkozy was born when I felt completely lost, I found a community that made me see myself. 

5. I cut ties w them who couldn’t love me without conditions
Even when they were family. Esp when they were family
I chose nervous system safety over inherited guilt 🧠🛼

I am still transitioning but I am grateful for the new life. If you are at a juncture of starting over, just start, it will give you innumerable breakdowns but growth only comes with challenges 💪🏻

from studygrammers at medikallyhappy & amedicodiary to @doctormuskaaan & @drkajalsinghh ✨

From prepping for NEET PG to working in NHS (Muskan) & switching career to non clinical (kj) we have come such a long long way, so proud of both of us, anxious but badass independent women that we have turned into, see you soon lolo☁️🍬

From a thought to a community☁️

When I started Medkozy, I just wanted to create a space where doctors could feel like themselves & be confident about being themselves beyond the hospital walls. A place where we could slow down, create, connect, and just be ourselves.✨

From Delhi to Bangalore, seeing @medkozy grow into a real, tangible community has been surreal. Strangers becoming friends, conversations flowing effortlessly, and everyone walking away with something more than what they came with. That’s the dream.🫶

In the first event we did vision  boarding, second was terrarium making & third one had: 

🖊️ Doodle Your Attendance
💐 DIY Bouquet Bar with MedBlossomBar
🎨 Pottery Painting
📝 “Pieces of Me” Reflection Game

Each brushstroke, each flower wrapped, each story shared, proves that we are more than just our profession.☁️🩺
